ctices]] team.\n\n== Celebrity appearances ==\nBetween July 2010 and July 2017, celebrities including [[Chris Pratt]], [[Jennifer Lawrence]], [[Woody Harrelson]], [[Carrie Underwood]], [[Brooklyn Decker]], [[Cee Lo Green]], [[Tom Skerritt]], [[Julie Bowen]], [[Chris Noth]], [[Paul Sorvino]], Alison Sweeney, and [[Julianne Moore]] have appeared in the program.  In that same time period, celebrity athletes including [[Phil Mickelson]], [[Joe Montana]], [[Jerry West]] and [[Jeff Burton]] have appeared on the program.\n\n== Format ==\nNewsWatch is hosted by Susan Bridges, Andrew Tropeano<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6726687/ IMDb: Andrew Tropeano - producer and director, known for NewsWatch (1989)] web page</ref><ref>[https://www.ceocfointerviews.com/interviews/AndrewTropeano-NewsWatchTV18.htm NewsWatch Newswatch TV Reviews Products to Better Inform Consumers, and they do it with Digital Media] web page</ref><ref>[https://epodcastnetwork.com/andrew-tropeano-effectively-informing-viewers-and-reviewing-products-with-newswatch-tv/ Andrew Tropeano: Effectively Informing Viewers and Reviewing Products with NewsWatch TV]</ref><ref>[https://ideamensch.com/andrew-tropeano/ Andrew Tropeano, Host and Co-Founder of NewsWatch] web page]</ref>, and Michelle Ison, who introduce individual stories and consumer oriented product/service reviews. Segments within the program typically run one-to-two minutes in length and are usually self-contained reports.\n\nThe host also conducts interviews with newsmakers in remote locations throughout the U.S. These interviews cover a multitude of topics and often include well-known celebrities who may have a personal involvement in the issue being discussed.\n\n=== Tech Report ===\nBeginning in April 2011, part of the NewsWatch program began a focus on the technology market, specifically new consumer focused technologies. Since April 2011, NewsWatch has worked with multiple [[Fortune 500]] companies to produce product reviews to air on the NewsWatch program. Recent Fortune 500 Technology reviews include [[Sony]], [[Siemens]]<ref>[http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/02/prweb12517927.htm Siemens Smart Hearing Aid Featured on NewsWatch Television] web page</ref> and Audi (part of [[Volkswagen Group]]).<ref>[http://newswatchtv.tumblr.com/post/138988652330/e-tron-quattro-concept E-Tron Quattro Concept Featured on NewsWatch Television] web page</ref>  Tech Report has featured other nationally recognized brands, including [[Outback Steakhouse]],<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/outback/videos/10153748298254387 NewsWatch TV reported on the features of the Outback App] web page</ref> Casio, Bang & Olufsen<ref>[http://technologylowdown.com/bang-and-olufsen-wireless-speaker-newswatch-review/ Bang and Olufsen \u2013 Wireless Speaker - NewsWatch Review] web page</ref> and D-Link.\n\n=== AppWatch ===\nStarting May 2012, NewsWatch began featuring AppWatch,<ref>[http://newswatchtv.com/appwatch.html AppWatch] web page</ref> a segment focused on finding and reviewing new and upcoming mobile apps for iOS, Android, and Windows devices.  AppWatch is hosted by Andrew Tropeano and runs weekly.  Recent AppWatch reviews included Intel<ref>[https://software.intel.com/en-us/blogs/2014/06/13/intel-tablets-showcased-on-the-history-and-bio-channel-feature-newswatch Intel\u00ae tablets showcased on the History and Bio Channel feature, NewsWatch] web page</ref> RCN Mobile App,<ref>http://www.rcn.com/about-rcn/newswatch-features-rcn-mobile-app</ref>  [[Jurassic Park III: Park Builder]], MoWeather,<ref>[http://www.moweather.com/?p=349 MoWeather on NewsWatch - AppWatch] web page</ref> AZ Pest Control,<ref>[http://www.pctonline.com/Arizona-Pest-Control-App-History-Channel.aspx PCTOnline - AZ Pest Control on History Channel] web page</ref> n8State,<ref>[http://www.consumerelectronicsnet.com/article/NewsWatch-Recently-Featured-the-N8-State-Mobile-Application-on-National-Television-2924796 Consumer Electronics Net - NewsWatch Recently Featured the N8 State Mobile Application on National Television] web page</ref> Lord of the Dragons, Baby's Brilliant,\n\n== Awards and recognition ==\nNewsWatch TV  won a Gold and Platinum 2017 Marcom Award for their nationwide 30 minute television program.<ref>[https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/newswatch-tv-wins-gold-in-television-awards-for-excellence-in-tv-production-and-product-reviews-300540707.html NewsWatch TV Wins Gold in Television Awards for Excellence in TV Production and Product Reviews] web page</ref><ref>[http://enter.marcomawards.com/winners/#/platinum/2017 2017 Marcom Platinum Award Winners] web page</ref> NewsWatch TV won the national 2017 Videographer Award for excellence in 30-minute entertainment programming.<ref>[http://technewsport.com/featured/newswatch-tv-wins-prestigious-videographer-award/ NewsWatch TV Wins Prestigious Videographer Award] web page</ref><ref>[https://enter.videoawards.com/winners/#/excellence/2017 2017 VideoGrapher Award Winners] web page</ref> The program received a 2016 Silver Telly Award, and was nominated for one other.<ref>[https://newswatchtv.com/2016/03/22/newswatch-nominated-for-two-telly-awards/ NewsWatch Nominated for Two Telly Awards] web page</ref>.  The program was awarded the Inc 5000 as one of the fastest growing media shows and companies in the United States. <ref>[https://www.inc.com/profile/newswatch NewsWatch Profile on Inc.com] web page</ref><ref>[https://www.dailyforexreport.com/newswatch-tv-honored-top-1000-inc-5000-list/ NewsWatch TV Honored in Top 1000 on the Inc. 5000 List] web page</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n* {{Citation\n  | title = Andrew Tropeano - IMDb. Producer and director, known for NewsWatch (1989)\n  | date = 15 Janaury 2020\n  | url = https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6726687/\n  | accessdate = 13 April 2020}}\n* {{Citation\n  | title = NewsWatch (TV Series 1989\u2013 ) - IMDb\n  | date = 1 February 2020\n  | url = https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3983740/\n  | accessdate = 13 April 2020}}\