)]]\n* [[Skin Deep (webcomic)|''Skin Deep'' (webcomic)]], a webcomic by Kory Bing\n\n==See also==\n* [[Deep (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Skin (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Skin depth]], in electronics\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n", "text_old": "'''Skin Deep''' may refer to:\n\n{{TOC right}}\n==Film==\n* [[Skin Deep (1922 film)|''Skin Deep'' (1922 film)]], a film by Lambert Hillyer\n* [[Skin Deep (1929 film)|''Skin Deep'' (1929 film)]], a film by Ray Enright\n* [[Skin Deep (1983 film)|''Skin Deep'' (1983 film)]], a film by Chris Langman and Mark Joffe\n* [[Skin Deep (1989 film)|''Skin Deep'' (1989 film)]], a film by Blake Edwards\n* [[Skin Deep (1995 film)|''Skin Deep'' (1995 film)]], a film by Midi Onodera\n\n==Television episodes==\n* [[Skin Deep (General Hospital: Night Shift)|\"Skin Deep\" (''General Hospital: Night Shift'')]]\n* [[Skin Deep (Grimm)|\"Skin Deep\" (''Grimm'')]]\n* [[Skin Deep (House)|\"Skin Deep\" (''House'')]]\n* [[Skin Deep (Once Upon a Time)|\"Skin Deep\" (''Once Upon a Time'')]]\n* [[Skin Deep (The Outer Limits)|\"Skin Deep\" (''The Outer Limits'')]]\n\n==Music==\n* [[Skin Deep (Louis Bellson album)|''Skin Deep'' (Louis Bellson album)]] (1995)\n** \"Skin Deep\", a composition by [[Louie Bellson]]\n* [[Skin Deep (Buddy Guy album)|''Skin Deep'' (Buddy Guy album)]] (2008)\n* [[Skin Deep (Sol\u00e9 album)|''Skin Deep'' (Sol\u00e9 album)]] (1999)\n* [[Skin Deep (Cher song)|\"Skin Deep\" (Cher song)]]\n* [[Skin Deep (The Stranglers song)|\"Skin Deep\" (The Stranglers song)]]\n* \"Skin Deep\", a song by Area-7 from ''[[Bitter & Twisted (album)|Bitter & Twisted]]''\n* \"Skin Deep\", a 1994 song by [[Guns n' Wankers]] from ''For Dancing and Listening''\n* ''Skin Deep'', a 2009 opera composed by [[David Sawer]] with a libretto by Armando Iannucci\n\n==Books==\n* ''Skin Deep. The Truth About Beauty Aids \u2013 Safe and Harmful'', a 1934 book by [[M.C. Phillips]]\n* ''Skin Deep'', a 1992 graphic novel by [[Charles Burns (cartoonist)|Charles Burns]]\n* ''Skin Deep'', a 1996 novel by [[Lois Ruby]]\n* ''Skin Deep: Inside the World of Black Fashion Models'', a 1998 non-fiction book by [[Barbara Summers]]\n\n== Other uses ==\n* [[Skin Deep (cosmetics database)]]\n* [[Skin Deep (webcomic)|''Skin Deep'' (webcomic)]], a webcomic by Kory Bing\n\n==See also==\n* [[Deep (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Skin (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Skin depth]], in electronics\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n", "name_user": "Zeete", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBooks:c/e", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_Deep"}
{"title_page": "International Bank of Azerbaijan", "text_new": "{{advert|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name             = International Bank of Azerbaijan\n| type             = [[Joint stock company#Post-Soviet Joint Stock Companies|Open Joint Stock Company]]\n| logo             = \n| logo_alt         = International Bank of Azerbaijan\n| foundation       = 10 January 1992\n| location_city    = [[Baku]]\n| location_country = [[Azerbaijan]]\n| key_people       = Chairman of the Board [[Abbas Ibrahimov]]\n|area_served       = \n| industry         = [[Bank]]ing\n|revenue           = \n|operating_income  = \n|net_income        = \n|assets            = \n|equity            = \n|products          = \n|subsid            = \n| num_employees    = \n| homepage         = http://www.ibar.az\n}}\nThe '''International Bank of Azerbaijan''' ({{lang-az|Az\u0259rbaycan Beyn\u0259lxalq Bank\u0131}}, {{IPA-az|\u0251z\u00e6rb\u0251j\u02c8d\u0361\u0292\u0251n b\u025bjn\u00e6l\u02c8x\u0251lk \u02c8b\u0251nk\u0259|}}) is a state-controlled entity operating in the Republic of Azerbaijan.\n\n==Bank history==\n\nThe bank started its activity in 1990 as a branch of the Russian bank. In 1992 the volume of the Bank grew and it became a full-share bank. The bank's headquarter is located in Baku. The International Bank of Azerbaijan is currently one of the leading banks in the South Caucasus region for its assets, customer base and international portfolio of operations. With 36 branches and 39 subbranches covering different regions of Azerbaijan, the Bank provides universal banking services to its retail and corporate customers. The number of legal entities serviced by the bank is more than 17,000 and the number of individuals is more than 1.3 million. The Bank employs more than 1,300 employees.\n\n==Service network==\n\nThe International Bank of Azerbaijan closely participates in large-scale state projects in such sectors as oil chemistry, transport, communications, energy and etc. and various social programs. At the same time, it actively supports the financing of large, small and medium-sized businesses.\n\nIn 1996, the International Bank of Azerbaijan established the processing card company \"AzerCard\", that served as a basis of card processing business in the country. In 1997, the Bank began cooperation with Visa and MasterCard, later the Bank expanded this activity and announced partnerships with such international payment systems as American Express, Union Pay, Diners Club and JCB. IBA is a local leader in terms of the number of international payment systems that are Bank\u2019s partners. The Bank offers its customers wide range of payment cards, such as VISA, MasterCard, American Express, and Union Pay. This bank is the first and only Bank of Azerbaijan to offer customers an opportunity to order American Express payment cards, as well as to hold operations with JCB cards.\n\nThe International Bank of Azerbaijan has the largest local network of ATM. Currently, there are about 800 ATMs, and over 13,000 POS terminals located at trade and service points covering in various regions of Azerbaijan.\nFor the first time ever in Azerbaijan, the International Bank of Azerbaijan has provided pension and wage payments through payment cards.\n\nAt present, the number of active payment cards of the bank exceeds 1 million 300 thousand. \nThinking about the convenience of customers, the International Bank of Azerbaijan has set up R@ndevu for the first time in the country. This service allows customers to make an appointment in advance and choose the date and time which are convenient to him and get priority service without waiting in line. In order to offer this software to its customers, the Bank has integrated eSirius software for the queue management system produced by France's ESII.\n\nIn 2002, the Bank established a subsidiary \u201cBank IBA-Moscow\u201d in the Russian Federation.\n\n==Board of Directors==\nIBA's Board of Directors includes seven members: \n* Chairman: Abbas Ibrahimov\n* The First Deputy Chairman: Ilham Habibullaev\n* Deputy Chairman: Vasif Akhmedov\n* Deputy Chairman: Taleh Tahirli\n* Deputy Chairman: Agshin Amirov\n* Deputy Chairman: Nabi Aliyev\n* Deputy Chairman: Elmir Habibullayev\n\n==Activity==\n\n===Mutual partnership relations===\nThe bank has received awards and recognition from organizations around the world. Some of these include the following:\n\n\"VISA PayWave\" and \"Mastercard PayPass\" payment technologies have been introduced in Azerbaijan for the first time by the International Bank of Azerbaijan.\n\nApplication of the \"Zero Liability\" policy within the framework of partnership with VISA is also the sole name of the International Bank of Azerbaijan.\n\n===Memberships===\nIBA is a member of the following professional organizations and systems:<ref>\n[http://www.ibar.az/index.php?in=Section&run=show&id=78 \u201cAbout Bank\u201d] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130122225339/http://www.ibar.az/index.php?in=Section&run=show&id=78 |date=2013-01-22 }}, International Bank of Azerbaijan \nwebsite\n</ref>\n* [[List of banks in Azerbaijan|Azerbaijan Banks Association (ABA)]]\n* [[Federation of Euro-Asian Stock Exchanges|Baku Stock Exchange (BSE)]]\n* [[Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunication|Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunication (SWIFT)]]\n* International payment system [[MasterCard|MasterCard International]]\n* International payment system [[Visa Inc.|VISA International]]\n* International payment system [[American Express]]\n* International information system [[Reuters]]\n* Azerbaijan-American Chamber of Commerce\n\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Banks}}\n* [[Azerbaijan]]\n* [[Azerbaijani manat]]\n* [[Banking in Azerbaijan]]\n* [[Central Bank of Azerbaijan]]\n* [[Economy of Azerbaijan]]\n* [[List of banks in Azerbaijan]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20131005014642/http://www.ibar.az/index.php?lang=en International Bank of Azerbaijan web site]\n\n {{IBARcorporatestructure}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:International Bank Of Azerbaijan}}\n[[Category:Government of Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Economy of Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Baku]]\n[[Category:Banks of Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Banks established in 1992]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani brands]]\n", "text_old": "{{advert|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name             = International Bank of Azerbaijan\n| type             = [[Joint stock company#Post-Soviet Joint Stock Companies|Open Joint Stock Company]]\n| logo             = \n| logo_alt         = International Bank of Azerbaijan\n| foundation       = 10 January 1992\n| location_city    = [[Baku]]\n| location_country = [[Azerbaijan]]\n| key_people       = Chairman of the Board [[Abbas Ibrahimov]]\n|area_served       = \n| industry         = [[Bank]]ing\n|revenue           = \n|operating_income  = \n|net_income        = \n|assets            = \n|equity            = \n|products          = \n|subsid            = \n| num_employees    = \n| homepage         = http://www.ibar.az\n}}\nThe '''International Bank of Azerbaijan''' ({{lang-az|Az\u0259rbaycan Beyn\u0259lxalq Bank\u0131}}, {{IPA-az|\u0251z\u00e6rb\u0251j\u02c8d\u0361\u0292\u0251n b\u025bjn\u00e6l\u02c8x\u0251lk \u02c8b\u0251nk\u0259|}}) is a state-controlled entity operating in the Republic of Azerbaijan.\n\n==Bank history==\n\nThe bank started its activity in 1990 as a branch of the Russian bank. In 1992 the volume of the Bank grew and it became a full-share bank. The bank's headquarter is located in Baku. The International Bank of Azerbaijan is currently one of the leading banks in the South Caucasus region for its assets, customer base and international portfolio of operations. With 35 branches and 39 subbranches covering different regions of Azerbaijan, the Bank provides universal banking services to its retail and corporate customers. The number o